# Ship workflow (musician-ai-studio)

When you finish a task that **changes tracked project files** (especially `www/`, `src/`, root `index.html` / `styles.css`, `api/`, or anything that affects the shipped web or native shell), do this **before ending the turn** unless the user explicitly says not to. **Do not wait for the user to say “commit / push / sync”** — they want this every time by default.

1. **`git status`** — confirm what changed.
2. If you edited anything under **`src/`** (especially `src/app.js`), **mirror into `www/src/`** before shipping native or testing Capacitor — e.g. `rsync -a src/ www/src/` from the repo root. The iOS shell loads **`www/`**, not `src/`; stale `www/src/app.js` is a common reason the footer build string and playback fixes never appear on device.
3. **`git add`** the relevant paths and **`git commit -m "…"`** with a short, accurate message (full sentences, no fluff).
4. **`git push`** to the current branch’s upstream (usually `origin main`). That is the deploy step for the web app when the GitHub repo is connected to Vercel; do not wait for the user to ask.
5. **`npx cap sync ios`** from the repo root so **`www`** is copied into **`ios/App/App/public`** and plugins/config stay aligned. If sync changes tracked files under `ios/`, commit and push those too in the same pass.

Skip only when there is **nothing to commit** (clean tree after sync) or the user asked to leave git alone. If push or sync fails, fix or report and do not claim success.
